HEADWORD: Duumvirate
<hw>Du*um"vi*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>duumviratus</ets>, fr. <ets>duumvir</ets>.]</ety> <def>The union of
two men in the same office; or the office, dignity, or government of two
men thus associated, as in ancient Rome.</def>⟦br⟧
